<TITLE> Strike at Akhaura land port </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Brahmanbaria, Feb 7 (bdnews24.com)  An indefinite strike by exporters-importers began at Akhaura land port from Saturday morning, following a dispute over the arrest of a Bangladeshi truck driver by Indian border security, said officials. "A Bangladeshi truck with valid papers, carrying stones, was stopped by the Indian Border Security Force last Wednesday," said Monir Hossain, general secretary of the Akhaura Landport Importer and Exporter Association. "The truck was seized, and driver Hafizuddin and helper Babul Mia were arrested," said Monir. The arrested were handed over to Bangladesh Customs and from there they ended up in Akhaura police custody, he added. "Unless the truck is returned and the arrested released, all import and exports will remain suspended," the association official. Akhaura customs officer Imtiaz Ahmed said: "Indian customs found Bangladeshi currency in the possession of the truck driver and his helper." "They have asked us to take measures," said Imtiaz. Rezaul Karim Bhuiyan, Akhaura police station officer in charge, said the arrested were sent to court Saturday under Section 54. bdnews24.com/correspon
